org.sbrubbles.genericcons
Class C<First,Rest>

java.lang.Object
  org.sbrubbles.genericcons.C<First,Rest>
Type Parameters:
First - The first type.
Rest - The last type, or a C holding the rest of the types.
public final class C<First,Rest>
extends Object

Captures and represents an open-ended list of types. This class isn't supposed to be instantiated or subclassed; it's used to build the list in the type declaration, like below: 

 Function<?, ?> f = new Function<String, C<Object, C<Number, C<String, Integer>>>>() {
   { // the no-arg constructor
     this.types = C.extractTypesFromSuperclass(this.getClass(), 1);
   }
 };
It was supposed to be called Cons (hence the C), but using only one letter kept type arguments (slightly) more readable.

Author:
Humberto Anjos

extractTypesFromSuperclass

public static List<? extends Type> extractTypesFromSuperclass(Class<?> baseClass,
                                                              int parameterIndex)
                                                       throws IllegalArgumentException,
                                                              TypeParametersNotFoundException
Searches the given base class' superclass for the list of types indexed by parameterIndex. Examples:
Generic SuperclassIndexOutput
Map<String, Integer>0[String]
Map<String, Integer>1[Integer]
Map<String, C<Number, Integer>>1[Number, Integer]
Map<String, C<Object, C<Number, Integer>>>0[String]
Map<String, C<Object, C<Number, Integer>>>1[Object, Number, Integer]
Map<String, C<Object, C<Number, Integer>>>2error: TypeParametersNotFoundException!
Object0error: TypeParametersNotFoundException!

Parameters:
baseClass - the class whose generic superclass holds the list of type arguments.
parameterIndex - where in the given base class' generic superclass' type argument list is the desired list of types.
Returns:
a list of the types found.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the given base class is null.
TypeParametersNotFoundException - if no type parameters are found.
